Patch Set 7: Library-Compliance-1

This library upgrade is outside of our upgrade policy (see https://gerrit-review.googlesource.com/Documentation/dev-contributing.html#_upgrading_libraries). Is there a reason why we need this upgrade now?

Patch Set 7:

> Patch Set 7: Library-Compliance-1
> 
> This library upgrade is outside of our upgrade policy (see https://gerrit-review.googlesource.com/Documentation/dev-contributing.html#_upgrading_libraries). Is there a reason why we need this upgrade now?

Say we create stable-3.0 today evening, in which case this change would be conform with Gerrit upgrade policy, would we get LC+1 then? Or would we get a different answer, that we would have to wait for internal approvals, or even yet another different answer, that we cannot upgrade too often internally, like here [1]?

* [1] https://gerrit-review.googlesource.com/c/gerrit/+/178051

Patch Set 7:

> Patch Set 7: Library-Compliance-1
> 
> This library upgrade is outside of our upgrade policy (see https://gerrit-review.googlesource.com/Documentation/dev-contributing.html#_upgrading_libraries). Is there a reason why we need this upgrade now?

Security update. We decided to skip 1.5.8 and go to 1.6.0.

Patch Set 7:

> or even yet another different answer, that we cannot upgrade too often internally, like here [1]?

To be fair, the statement there was "we can't upgrade this internally very fast", which to my understanding means because of not having the resources to work on it.  I.e. it's not about the frequency of the updates ("too often").

Patch Set 7:

> Patch Set 7:
> 
> > Patch Set 7: Library-Compliance-1
> > 
> > This library upgrade is outside of our upgrade policy (see https://gerrit-review.googlesource.com/Documentation/dev-contributing.html#_upgrading_libraries). Is there a reason why we need this upgrade now?
> 
> Security update. We decided to skip 1.5.8 and go to 1.6.0.

As I said on the 1.5.8 update change, I don't think the security issue is a threat to Gerrit in the way that we use asciidoctor (i.e. at build time, rather than runtime).

That said, if the security fix IS the motivation for the upgrade, then it should be explicitly mentioned in the commit message.

Patch Set 8:

> Patch Set 7:

> > Patch Set 7:
> > 
> > > Patch Set 7: Library-Compliance-1
> > > 
> > > This library upgrade is outside of our upgrade policy (see https://gerrit-review.googlesource.com/Documentation/dev-contributing.html#_upgrading_libraries). Is there a reason why we need this upgrade now?
> > 
> > Security update. We decided to skip 1.5.8 and go to 1.6.0.
> 
> As I said on the 1.5.8 update change, I don't think the security issue is a threat to Gerrit in the way that we use asciidoctor (i.e. at build time, rather than runtime).
> 
> That said, if the security fix IS the motivation for the upgrade, then it should be explicitly mentioned in the commit message.

Thanks, David. Most of the time, the internal updates take considerable amount of time for us and knowing which updates are important and for which reason helps to prioritize.

@David O.: Yes, we need an internal update, which I added to our internal task list. Otherwise I would have given LC+1 or suggested to cut a new branch. I'll try to phrase my comment more clearly next time.
